x4freetext: 100 ug/cm2 thick target with a 12 ug/cm2 layer of
evaporated 197Au was used for the measurements at
and a target 124 ug/cm2 thick with 20 ug/cm2 197Au
layer for Ec.m. = 17.65 and 19.33 MeV
197Au target 150 ug/cm2 thick was used in subsequent
runs for calibration purpose.
An array of eight planar silicon surface-
barrier detectors, 150 um thick, with an angular
separation of 5 degree between adjacent detectors.
These detectors were mounted in a 70-cm-diameter
scattering chamber.
Two separate silicon surface-barrier detectors
were kept fixed at the most backward angles of
160.0 and 168.1 degree for all measurements.
Two monitors, silicon detectors, were placed at
forward angles +/- 16.0 degree related to the beam
direction for the absolute normalization purpose.

forward to most backward angles for the lower
energies and 0.2% to 27% for the highest energy of
Ec.m. = 29.41 MeV.
